.TH "intel_scu_ipc_dev_update" 9 "intel_scu_ipc_dev_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_scu_ipc_dev_update \- Update a register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" intel_scu_ipc_dev_update
.BI "(struct intel_scu_ipc_dev *scu "  ","
.BI "u16 addr "  ","
.BI "u8 data "  ","
.BI "u8 mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "scu" 12
Optional SCU IPC instance
.IP "addr" 12
Register address
.IP "data" 12
Bits to update
.IP "mask" 12
Mask of bits to update
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read-modify-write power control unit register. The first data argument
must be register value and second is mask value mask is a bitmap that
indicates which bits to update. 0 = masked. Don't modify this bit, 1 =
modify this bit. returns 0 on success or an error code.

This function may sleep. Locking between SCU accesses is handled
for the caller.
